---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
import { getAffiliateCTA } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const tools = [
  { name: 'Durable AI', slug: '/reviews/durable-ai', score: '8.5', freeTrial: 'Yes', freeForever: 'No' },
  { name: 'Mixo AI', slug: '/reviews/mixo-ai', score: '8.5', freeTrial: 'Yes', freeForever: 'No' },
  { name: 'Relume AI', slug: '/reviews/relume-ai', score: '8.3', freeTrial: 'Yes', freeForever: 'Yes (limited)' },
  { name: 'Pineapple', slug: '/reviews/pineapple-ai', score: '7.9', freeTrial: 'Yes', freeForever: 'No' },
  { name: 'Unicorn', slug: '/reviews/unicorn-ai', score: '7.5', freeTrial: 'Yes', freeForever: 'No' }
];
---

<Layout title="Free AI Website Builders: What's the Catch?">
  <StructuredData type="WebPage" data={{ name: 'Free AI Website Builders Comparison', description: 'Compare free AI website builders. Durable, Mixo, Relume, Pineapple, Unicorn. What you get vs paid plans.', url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/comparisons/free-ai-builders-comparison' }} />

  <section class="bg-[#FFF8F0] py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] mb-6">
        <span class="text-xs font-black">Jan 2025 · FREE BUILDER GUIDE</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black">Free AI Website Builders:<span class="block text-[#F5521A]">What's the Catch?</span></h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mt-6">I tested 5 "free" AI builders. Here's what they actually give you.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">The "Free" Truth</h2>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-[3px] border-yellow-400 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="font-bold text-yellow-800">Reality Check: None of these are truly free. They're free trials with limitations. You'll need to pay to get useful features.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-black mb-4">Quick Comparison</h3>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full bg-white rounded-xl border-[3px] border-gray-200">
          <thead class="bg-gray-900 text-white">
            <tr><th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Builder</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">Score</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">Free Trial</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">Free Forever</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">Catch</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Durable AI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-[#F5521A]">8.5/10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Yes (30 days)</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">No</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-sm">Need paid for custom domain</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Mixo AI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-[#F5521A]">8.5/10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Yes</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">No</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-sm">Subdomain, Mixo branding</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Relume AI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">8.3/10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Yes</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">Yes (limited)</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-sm">Planning only, not hosting</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Pineapple</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">7.9/10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Yes</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">No</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-sm">Restaurant-focused only</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Unicorn</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">7.5/10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">Yes</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">No</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-sm">Very basic features</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- My Experience -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-6 md:p-8 rounded-xl">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">My Experience: The "Free" Trap That Wasted 3 Weeks</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">Real testing, not theoretical comparison</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Three years ago, a client insisted on starting with a "free" AI builder. Budget was zero—bootstrapping mode. I should have pushed back harder.</p>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>The free route:</strong> Signed up for Mixo free plan. Generated landing page in 52 seconds. Looked okay. Published to mixo-builder.com/sitename subdomain. Client thrilled—didn't cost a cent.</p>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Two weeks in: Client wanted custom domain. "That'll be $9/month to upgrade." Passed—still using free subdomain.</p>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Three weeks in: Needed more than 3 pages. "That's $19/month for the premium plan." Client declined.</p>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Month 2: Site getting traffic. "Made with Mixo" badge looking unprofessional. "Remove branding requires paid plan." Client still refused.</p>

          <div class="bg-red-100 border-l-[4px] border-red-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-red-900 font-medium"><strong>The breaking point:</strong> Month 3, client landed big opportunity. Potential partner visited site, saw "Made with Mixo" badge on subdomain URL. Said "looks amateurish, call us when you have a real site." Deal worth $12,000/year vanished. Client called me in tears.</p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Upgraded to Mixo premium ($19/month). Bought custom domain ($12/year). Spent 3 hours rebranding the site. Total damage: $12,000 opportunity cost + $240/year going forward to save $19/month initially.</p>

          <div class="bg-orange-100 border-l-[4px] border-orange-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-orange-900 font-medium"><strong>The lesson:</strong> "Free" plans are trials. They're for testing, not production. If you're serious about business, pay from day one. The subdomain, builder branding, and feature limitations scream "side project" not "real business."</p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>The exception that worked:</strong> A hobby blogger testing different niches. Used Relume free tier to plan 4 different site structures. Never published—just planning. Found the right niche after 3 weeks, then paid for Framer to build properly.</p>

          <div class="bg-yellow-100 border-l-[4px] border-yellow-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-yellow-900 font-medium"><strong>Free tier done right:</strong> Relume free tier was perfect—genuine value without limitations that block progress. But Relume's a planning tool, not hosting. Different use case.</p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>The brutal truth:</strong> If you're building a real business, "free" costs more than paid. Subdomain hurts SEO. Builder branding kills credibility. Feature limitations waste time when you outgrow them. Pay $15/month from day one or don't bother.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">The Catches</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-red-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">1. Custom Domain Costs Money</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">All "free" plans put your site on a subdomain (yoursite.builder.com). To use your own domain, you must pay.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">2. Builder Branding</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">Free plans often show "Made with X" badges. You can't remove these without paying.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">3. Limited Features</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">Free tiers limit pages, storage, bandwidth, and features. You'll hit a ceiling quickly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-red-700 mb-2">4. No Code Export</h3>
          <p class="text-sm">Almost none let you export on free plans. If you leave, you lose everything.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Best Free Option</h2>
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-[3px] border-green-400 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Relume AI - Truly Free Planning</h3>
        <p class="text-sm mb-4">Relume is the only one that's actually useful for free. You get sitemap generation, wireframing, and component libraries. It's a planning tool, not hosting - but it's genuinely free forever.</p>
        <p class="text-sm"><strong>Use case:</strong> Plan your site in Relume, then build in Framer or Webflow.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">My Recommendation</h2>
      <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl p-6 text-white">
        <p class="text-base mb-4">Don't expect a production-ready site for free. These are trials. The "free" tier is to test the builder before committing.</p>
        <p class="text-base mb-4"><strong class="text-[#F5521A]">Best approach:</strong> Use free trials to test 2-3 builders. Pick the one you like best. Then pay for a plan - it's worth it for a real business.</p>
        <p class="text-base"><strong class="text-[#F5521A]">Budget tip:</strong> Framer ($15/mo) and Durable ($15/mo) are the most affordable paid plans that still give you useful features.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
